name for Vyond remains as \"GoAnimate, Inc.\".{{Citation needed|date=July 2018}}\n\nOn May 6, 2019, Vyond announced the retirement  of the legacy video maker, due to the end-of-life of [[Adobe Flash|Flash]]. It was planned to be retired on December 16, 2019, but was eventually retired on December 18, 2019. All user accounts defaulted to Vyond Studio on August 14, 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vyond.com/blog/legacy-video-maker-retirement/|title=Legacy Video Maker Retirement|website=www.vyond.com|language=en|access-date=2019-07-20}}</ref>\n\n== Product ==\nVyond provides its users with a library containing tens of thousands of pre-animated assets, which can be controlled through a drag & drop interface. Asset types include characters, actions, templates, props, text boxes, music tracks and sound effects. Users can also upload their own assets, such as audio files, image files or video files. There is also a drag & drop composition tool, which users can employ to create pans and zooms.\n\nSpoken dialogue and narration can be recorded directly into the platform or imported as an audio file. Characters can automatically lip-sync dialogue that is assigned to them. Alternatively, audio can be set as voiceover narration. Users can download their finished videos as MP4 files, [[GIF]]s or video presentations. They can also export them directly to a variety of video hosting sites including [[YouTube]], [[Wistia]], [[Vidyard]], [[Vimeo]], [[Vzaar]] and [[WeVideo]].\n\nA version for schools was also available, called GoAnimate for Schools. On April 10, 2018, Vyond announced that GoAnimate for Schools would be shut down on June 30, 2019. On that same day, GoAnimate removed its 14 day free trial to the schools site. Subscription purchases and renewals on goanimate4schools.com were later removed on May 6, 2018, with product support and service officially terminating on June 30, 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://blog.goanimate4schools.com/2018/04/10/goanimate-for-schools-is-shutting-down/|title=GoAnimate for Schools is Shutting Down|date=2018-04-10|access-date=2018-04-11}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vyond.com/company/press/|title=Press {{!}} Vyond|website=www.vyond.com|language=en|access-date=2018-06-07}}</ref>\n\n==Grounded videos==\nOn [[YouTube]], a subculture of videos that utilize Vyond emerged in the past, they were created by a user called  adamkleinschmidt2003 in 2011, though it has declined with the site's more expensive service fees. Known colloquially known as \"grounded videos\" or \"punishment day videos\", these videos usually feature the protagonist characters from animated children's programs such as ''[[Caillou]]'' and ''[[Dora the Explorer]]'' being out of character and generally getting into trouble, resulting in their punishments being disproportionate. Generally, this is a [[Grounding (discipline technique)|grounding]] for an absurd amount of time from an authority figure, usually longer than a human's natural lifetime (such as a century or multiple decades, often exaggerated into billions of years), or can be as extreme as immediate [[capital punishment]] carried out by law enforcement. These are usually created with the intent of comedic effect, as the [[Speech synthesis|text-to-speech]] system Vyond uses to provide voices can fail to recognize the large numbers used in those videos, and often reads onomatopoeic sounds as literal words rather than expressions.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.geek.com/culture/internet-gutter-grounded-videos-1655814/|title=Internet Gutter: Grounded videos|website=Geek.com|date=2016-08-03|accessdate=2019-09-10}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{official website|http://vyond.com/}}\n\n[[Category:Animation software]]\n[[Category:Marketing companies established in 2007]]\n[[Category:2007 establishments in California]]\n[[Category:Privately held companies based in California]]\n[[Category:Companies based in San Mateo, California]]\n[[Category:Websites about animation]]\n[[Category:Internet properties established in 2007]]\n[[Category:American companies established in 2007]]\n[[Category:Software companies based in the San Francisco Bay Area]]\n[[Category:Technology companies established in 2007]]\n[[Category:Software companies of the United States]]\n", "name_user": "Majavah", "label": "safe", "comment": "clean up,typo(s) fixed: 14 day \u2192 14-day, \u2019s \u2192 's (2)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vyond"}
{"title_page": "Paek Nam-un", "text_new": "{{Infobox officeholder\n|name         = Paek Nam-un\n|image        = \n|caption      = \n|office       = \n|order        = \n|term_start   = \n|term_end     = \n|deputy       = \n|1blankname   = \n|1namedata    = \n|predecessor  = \n|successor    = \n|birth_name   = \n|birth_date   =  {{birth date|1894|02|11|mf=y}}\n|birth_place  = [[North Hamgyong Province]], [[Korea under Japanese rule|Japanese Korea]]\n|death_date   = {{death date and age|1979|6|12|1900|10|20|mf=y}}\n|death_place  = \n|death_cause = \n|religion     = \n|nickname     = \n|allegiance   = {{flag|North Korea}}\n|branch       = \n|serviceyears = \n|rank         =  \n|commands     = \n|battles      = \n|education    =\n|alma_mater   = [[Communist University of the Toilers of the East]]\n|awards      = \n|party        = [[Workers' Party of Korea]]\n}}\n'''Paek Nam-un ({{lang-ko|\ubc31\ub0a8\uc6b4}})''' (February 11, 1894 \u2013 June 12, 1979) is an economist, educator and politician during the Japanese colonial period and following the establishment of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea. He was a professor of economics at Yeonhee College and an economic theorist of the Communist Party of Korea, and a representative figure of socialist economists during the Japanese colonial period along with Lee Soon-Tak. After the independence, on the premise of some asset class and solidarity, in the article 'The Path of the Chosun People's', 'Combination of New Democracy (National Unification Front)' was proposed. After liberation, Kim Doo-bong, Heo Jeong-suk, and Choi Chang-ik connected with Nam Joseon New Democratic Party and Nationalist Democratic Front, but did not come down after coming to North Korea with Kim Gu, Kim Kyu-sik, Jang Geon-sang in April 1948. Since then, he served as the first literary statue of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea and the chairman of the Supreme People's Assembly.\n\n==Biography==\n===Early life===\nBorn in Gochang-gun, Jeonbuk Province in 1894. In 1912, at the age of 19, he entered Suwon Agriculture and Forestry School. The school was free of tuition, was able to live in a dormitory, and Nam Wun Baek was even subsidized in tuition, so he was able to concentrate on his studies. After graduating from Suwon Agricultural and Forestry School in 1915, he was appointed as a teacher at Ganghwa Normal School in accordance with the mandatory regulations.\n\nAfter working for two years at this school, he received a telegram as an engineer of the Ganghwa-gun Forestry Cooperative and worked again for one year. He wandered worrying about the future of this period and decided to study in Japan for a new intellectual desire. In 1918, he went to Japan to study, graduated from Tokyo High School of Commerce and Tokyo University of Commerce (now Hitotsubashi University).\n\nAfter graduating from Tokyo University in 1925, he returned to Korea and became a professor at Yonhee College. During this period, in 1925, the Communist Party of Korea was founded in secret. Although communism had already been introduced to Korea, which had fallen into a colony, even after the founding of the Communist Party of Korea and the Korean Studies Movement in the 1920s, the Governor-General of Japan made a series of suppression of the communist movement and the Korean history of restructuring. Nevertheless, socialism was persistently spreading in connection with the anti-Japanese movement.\n\n===Late Japanese colonial period===\nHe stood in the position of Marx's antiquities and class struggle theory and lectured on the history of Joseon, criticizing and refuting the 'identity theory' of the colonial consulate, and along with the lecture activities, he wrote books, Korea Social Economic History in 1933 and Korea Feudal Society in 1937 about economic history. On the other hand, Paek Nam-un was attacked intensively by people in the autonomous movement when he published several criticisms of autonomy asserted by national reformists from a nationalist perspective.\n\nAs his reputation as an economist became known, there were many students following him, and Nam Woon Baek led a socialist student club called the Economic Research Society. However, the Japanese imprisoned him and imprisoned him for more than two years. Released in 1940, he later lived in seclusion in addition to interacting with scholars.\n\n===After liberation===\nWith Nam Wun Baek, on August 15, 1945, first founded the Korea Academy and became professor of the Faculty of Law, [[Kyungsung University]]. He then devoted progressive or socialist scholars to supporting the theory of building a new nation.<ref name=autogenerated1>[http://www.donga.com/fbin/output?sfrm=2&n=199511220290]</ref>\nIn December 1945, when the Moscow 3-phase conference was announced, he first declared a return in the name of the president of the Korea Academy and insisted on it through lectures, but later turned to a stand and supported the stand.\n\nFrom this point on, Paek Nam-un began to work on the political front. He was independence movement in Yan'an, China, and had a certain connection with Hangul scholar Kim Doo-bong, who returned to the north of the [[Division of Korea|38th parallel]], Choi Chang-ik of the Korean Independent Alliance, and Jung-sook Heo. Paek Nam-un organized the Gyeongseong Special Committee of the Korean Independent Alliance and became Chairman. Then, with the consent of Kim Doo-bong, a party called the Nam Josun New Democratic Party was founded and progressively reorganized to become the party leader. Connected with Kim Doo-bong, Heo Jung-sook, and Choi Chang-ik, and worked with the Namjosun New Democratic Party in the National Democracy Front in February 1946.\n\n====New Democratic Party Activities====\nHe has been to the north of the 38th parallel twice as a representative of the New Democratic Party of Namjosun. In addition, the Korean military campaigned for unification in the midst of US military campaigns. Thus, the New Korea People's Party, the People's Party of Korea, and the [[Communist Party of Korea]] were worthy to form the South Korean Workers' Party. On February 15, 1946, he was invited to the co-chair of the Nationalist National Front (Minjeon).<ref>\uac15\uc900\ub9cc, \ud55c\uad6d\ud604\ub300\uc0ac\uc0b0\ucc45 1940\ub144\ub300\ud3b8 1\uad8c 211\ucabd</ref> He left the street without joining the Namro Party, led by Park Heon-young, and through this, he had a conflict and confrontation with Park Heon-young. During this process, he felt skeptical and declared resignation in front of the barriers of reality. After that, he organized the National Culture Research Center and participates in cultural movements. However, in April 1947, six months after the retirement of the political system, the government returned to the political system. After announcing an article against the establishment of a single government, he collaborated with Yeon-hyung Yeo to join the founding of the People's Party of Korea. In May 1947, he was appointed Vice-Chairman of the People's Party of Korea. However, on July 19, when Yeon-hyung was assassinated, he could no longer maintain his organization. In August 1947, a wave of left-wing arrest arrested Paek Nam-un in a crisis of being arrested with the party. Eventually, Nam Woon Baek faces a threat of personal affairs, and first brings the family to North Korea.\n\nBy the time he was studying in Japan, he was strongly influenced by Marxism in the intellectual class in Japan, and there were many socialist economists, especially in Tokyo. From this point on, it is estimated that Paek Nam-un naturally leaned toward Marxism.<ref name=autogenerated1 />\n[[image:\ud5c8\ud5cc \ubc15\ud5cc\uc601 \ud64d\uba85\ud76c.jpg|thumb|right|200px|In August 1948, the 'People's Congress' was held in [[Haeju]], [[Hwanghae Province]]. From the left, Paek Nam-un, Heo Heon, [[Pak Hon-yong]], and [[Hong Myong-hui]].]]\nOn May 10, 1948, the general election was scheduled to go north or south of South Korea. At the crossroads, Paek Nam-un chose to participate in the inter-Korean negotiations with Kim Gu, criticizing the establishment of the 'South Korea Bay Government' and the May 10 general election. In April 1948, he attended the Pyongyang Inter-Korean Conference. At this conference, he first gave a speech following Kim Il-sung and Park Heon-young, and at the third meeting he was also the moderator.\n\nHe was the twelfth northbound and the last northbound to go north to participate in inter-Korean negotiations. After that, he sat down in Pyongyang after the inter-Korean negotiations.<ref name=autogenerated1 />\n\n===North Korea===\nAugust\u2013September 1948 The 1st Expeditionary Member of the Supreme People's Assembly of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea. He was appointed as the first Education Minister in the [[Cabinet of North Korea|North Korean Cabinet]] led by [[Premier of North Korea|Premier]] [[Kim Il-sung]] and served for eight years. He also served as President of the Academy of Sciences of North Korea. Afterwards, the distance from the coastal group was safe when Kim Doo-bong and Choi Chang-ik were purged and Hur Jeong-suk was displaced in 1961. Later he served as the Vice Chairman of the Standing Committee of the Supreme People's Assembly in 1961\u201362, the Central Committee of the Korean Workers' Party, Marx Leninist Broadcasting University. He became the President of the Supreme People's Assembly in 1967, and the Chairman of the National Democratic Front of Korea in 1974.<ref name=autogenerated1 />\n\nPaek Nam-un acted as an intermediary for North Korea's intellectuals. On his first trip to the Northern part of Korea in January 1946, he was asked by the Democratic People's Republic of Korea to arrange for North Korea, such as a professor of South Korean scientists and artists, and returned to Seoul, inviting intellectuals to historian Kim Seok-hyung and Park Si-hyung, textile industry authority physicist, physicist It is known that Sang-rok Do, engineer Jae-woo Choi and Young-chang Kang, and artists Yeol-bong Moon, Chul-hwan Hwang, and Young-sin Park were arranged.\n\nHe was elected to the [[Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea|Central Committee]] of the [[Workers' Party of Korea]] in 1961, and was elected chairman of the Supreme People's Assembly in 1967, serving in that post until 1972. After that, he served as chairman of the Democratic Front of the Fatherland and died in 1979 at the age of 86.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{S-start}}\n{{S-off}}\n{{s-bef|before = [[Ho Hon]]}}\n{{S-ttl|title=[[President of the Presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly|Chairman of the Supreme People's Assembly]]\n|years=1957-1972}}\n{{S-aft|after=[[Han Duk-su]]|}}\n\n[[Category:Members of the Supreme People's Assembly]]\n[[Category:Workers' Party of Korea politicians]]\n[[Category:Korean communists]]\n[[Category:1894 births]]\n[[Category:1979 deaths]]\n[[Category:North Korean politicians]]\n[[Category:Government ministers of North Korea]]\n\n[[ko:\ubc31\ub0a8\uc6b4]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox officeholder\n|name         = Paek Nam-un\n|image        = \n|caption      = \n|office       = \n|order        = \n|term_start   = \n|term_end     = \n|deputy       = \n|1blankname   = \n|1namedata    = \n|predecessor  = \n|successor    = \n|birth_name   = \n|birth_date   =  {{birth date|1894|02|11|mf=y}}\n|birth_place  = [[North Hamgyong Province]], [[Korea under Japanese rule|Japanese Korea]]\n|death_date   = {{death date and age|1979|6|12|1900|10|20|mf=y}}\n|death_place  = \n|death_cause = \n|religion     = \n|nickname     = \n|allegiance   = {{flag|North Korea}}\n|branch       = \n|serviceyears = \n|rank         =  \n|commands     = \n|battles      = \n|education    =\n|alma_mater   = [[Communist University of the Toilers of the East]]\n|awards      = \n|party        = [[Workers' Party of Korea]]\n}}\n'''Paek Nam-un ({{lang-ko|\ubc31\ub0a8\uc6b4}})''' (February 11, 1894 \u2013 June 12, 1979) is an economist, educator and politician during the Japanese colonial period and following the establishment of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea. He was a professor of economics at Yeonhee College and an economic theorist of the Communist Party of Korea, and a representative figure of socialist economists during the Japanese colonial period along with Lee Soon-Tak. After the independence, on the premise of some asset class and solidarity, in the article 'The Path of the Chosun People's', 'Combination of New Democracy (National Unification Front)' was proposed. After liberation, Kim Doo-bong, Heo Jeong-suk, and Choi Chang-ik connected with Nam Joseon New Democratic Party and Nationalist Democratic Front, but did not come down after coming to North Korea with Kim Gu, Kim Kyu-sik, Jang Geon-sang in April 1948. Since then, he served as the first literary statue of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea and the chairman of the Supreme People's Assembly.\n\n==Biography==\n===Early life===\nBorn in Gochang-gun, Jeonbuk Province in 1894. In 1912, at the age of 19, he entered Suwon Agriculture and Forestry School. The school was free of tuition, was able to live in a dormitory, and Nam Wun Baek was even subsidized in tuition, so he was able to concentrate on his studies. After graduating from Suwon Agricultural and Forestry School in 1915, he was appointed as a teacher at Ganghwa Normal School in accordance with the mandatory regulations.\n\nAfter working for two years at this school, he received a telegram as an engineer of the Ganghwa-gun Forestry Cooperative and worked again for one year. He wandered worrying about the future of this period and decided to study in Japan for a new intellectual desire. In 1918, he went to Japan to study, graduated from Tokyo High School of Commerce and Tokyo University of Commerce (now Hitotsubashi University).\n\nAfter graduating from Tokyo University in 1925, he returned to Korea and became a professor at Yonhee College. During this period, in 1925, the Communist Party of Korea was founded in secret. Although communism had already been introduced to Korea, which had fallen into a colony, even after the founding of the Communist Party of Korea and the Korean Studies Movement in the 1920s, the Governor-General of Japan made a series of suppression of the communist movement and the Korean history of restructuring. Nevertheless, socialism was persistently spreading in connection with the anti-Japanese movement.\n\n===Late Japanese colonial period===\nHe stood in the position of Marx's antiquities and class struggle theory and lectured on the history of Joseon, criticizing and refuting the 'identity theory' of the colonial consulate, and along with the lecture activities, he wrote books, Korea Social Economic History in 1933 and Korea Feudal Society in 1937 about economic history. On the other hand, Paek Nam-un was attacked intensively by people in the autonomous movement when he published several criticisms of autonomy asserted by national reformists from a nationalist perspective.\n\nAs his reputation as an economist became known, there were many students following him, and Nam Woon Baek led a socialist student club called the Economic Research Society. However, the Japanese imprisoned him and imprisoned him for more than two years. Released in 1940, he later lived in seclusion in addition to interacting with scholars.\n\n===After liberation===\nWith Nam Wun Baek, on August 15, 1945, first founded the Korea Academy and became professor of the Faculty of Law, [[Kyungsung University]]. He then devoted progressive or socialist scholars to supporting the theory of building a new nation.<ref name=autogenerated1>[http://www.donga.com/fbin/output?sfrm=2&n=199511220290]</ref>\nIn December 1945, when the Moscow 3-phase conference was announced, he first declared a return in the name of the president of the Korea Academy and insisted on it through lectures, but later turned to a stand and supported the stand.\n\nFrom this point on, Paek Nam-un began to work on the political front. He was independence movement in Yan'an, China, and had a certain connection with Hangul scholar Kim Doo-bong, who returned to the north of the [[Division of Korea|38th parallel]], Choi Chang-ik of the Korean Independent Alliance, and Jung-sook Heo. Paek Nam-un organized the Gyeongseong Special Committee of the Korean Independent Alliance and became Chairman. Then, with the consent of Kim Doo-bong, a party called the Nam Josun New Democratic Party was founded and progressively reorganized to become the party leader. Connected with Kim Doo-bong, Heo Jung-sook, and Choi Chang-ik, and worked with the Namjosun New Democratic Party in the National Democracy Front in February 1946.\n\n====New Democratic Party Activities====\nHe has been to the north of the 38th parallel twice as a representative of the New Democratic Party of Namjosun. In addition, the Korean military campaigned for unification in the midst of US military campaigns. Thus, the New Korea People's Party, the People's Party of Korea, and the [[Communist Party of Korea]] were worthy to form the South Korean Workers' Party. On February 15, 1946, he was invited to the co-chair of the Nationalist National Front (Minjeon).<ref>\uac15\uc900\ub9cc, \ud55c\uad6d\ud604\ub300\uc0ac\uc0b0\ucc45 1940\ub144\ub300\ud3b8 1\uad8c 211\ucabd</ref> He left the street without joining the Namro Party, led by Park Heon-young, and through this, he had a conflict and confrontation with Park Heon-young. During this process, he felt skeptical and declared resignation in front of the barriers of reality. After that, he organized the National Culture Research Center and participates in cultural movements. However, in April 1947, six months after the retirement of the political system, the government returned to the political system. After announcing an article against the establishment of a single government, he collaborated with Yeon-hyung Yeo to join the founding of the People's Party of Korea. In May 1947, he was appointed Vice-Chairman of the People's Party of Korea. However, on July 19, when Yeon-hyung was assassinated, he could no longer maintain his organization. In August 1947, a wave of left-wing arrest arrested Paek Nam-un in a crisis of being arrested with the party. Eventually, Nam Woon Baek faces a threat of personal affairs, and first brings the family to North Korea.\n\nBy the time he was studying in Japan, he was strongly influenced by Marxism in the intellectual class in Japan, and there were many socialist economists, especially in Tokyo. From this point on, it is estimated that Paek Nam-un naturally leaned toward Marxism.<ref name=autogenerated1 />\n[[image:\ud5c8\ud5cc \ubc15\ud5cc\uc601 \ud64d\uba85\ud76c.jpg|thumb|right|200px|In August 1948, the 'People's Congress' was held in [[Haeju]], [[Hwanghae Province]]. From the left, Paek Nam-un, Heo Heon, [[Pak Hon-yong]], and [[Hong Myong-hui]].]]\nOn May 10, 1948, the general election was scheduled to go north or south of South Korea. At the crossroads, Paek Nam-un chose to participate in the inter-Korean negotiations with Kim Gu, criticizing the establishment of the 'South Korea Bay Government' and the May 10 general election. In April 1948, he attended the Pyongyang Inter-Korean Conference. At this conference, he first gave a speech following Kim Il-sung and Park Heon-young, and at the third meeting he was also the moderator.\n\nHe was the twelfth northbound and the last northbound to go north to participate in inter-Korean negotiations. After that, he sat down in Pyongyang after the inter-Korean negotiations.<ref name=autogenerated1 />\n\n===North Korea===\nAugust\u2013September 1948 The 1st Expeditionary Member of the Supreme People's Assembly of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea. He was appointed as the first Education Minister in the [[Cabinet of North Korea|North Korean Cabinet]] led by [[Premier of North Korea|Premier]] [[Kim Il-sung]] and served for eight years. He also served as President of the Academy of Sciences of North Korea. Afterwards, the distance from the coastal group was safe when Kim Doo-bong and Choi Chang-ik were purged and Hur Jeong-suk was displaced in 1961. Later he served as the Vice Chairman of the Standing Committee of the Supreme People's Assembly in 1961\u201362, the Central Committee of the Korean Workers' Party, Marx Leninist Broadcasting University. He became the President of the Supreme People's Assembly in 1967, and the Chairman of the National Democratic Front of Korea in 1974.<ref name=autogenerated1 />\n\nPaek Nam-un acted as an intermediary for North Korea's intellectuals. On his first trip to the Northern part of Korea in January 1946, he was asked by the Democratic People's Republic of Korea to arrange for North Korea, such as a professor of South Korean scientists and artists, and returned to Seoul, inviting intellectuals to historian Kim Seok-hyung and Park Si-hyung, textile industry authority physicist, physicist It is known that Sang-rok Do, engineer Jae-woo Choi and Young-chang Kang, and artists Yeol-bong Moon, Chul-hwan Hwang, and Young-sin Park were arranged.\n\nHe was elected to the [[Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea|Central Committee]] of the [[Workers' Party of Korea]] in 1961, and was elected chairman of the Supreme People's Assembly in 1967, serving in that post until 1972. After that, he served as chairman of the Democratic Front of the Fatherland and died in 1979 at the age of 86.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Members of the Supreme People's Assembly]]\n[[Category:Workers' Party of Korea politicians]]\n[[Category:Korean communists]]\n[[Category:1894 births]]\n[[Category:1979 deaths]]\n[[Category:North Korean politicians]]\n[[Category:Government ministers of North Korea]]\n\n[[ko:\ubc31\ub0a8\uc6b4]]\n", "name_user": "Rakoon", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Paek_Nam-un"}
{"title_page": "Arjun Mark", "text_new": "= Arjun Mark =\n'''Arjun Mark''' (born 1980) is an acclaimed Indian [[Fashion photography|fashion photographer]] regarded for his bold and modern aesthetic. He is recognised for being listed on '''[[L\u00fcrzer's Archive|L\u00dcRZER'S ARCHIVE'S]]''' 200 Best Ad Photographers Worldwide 2020/21<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.luerzersarchive.com/en/magazine/print-detail/arjun-mark-70877.html|title=Arjun Mark|website=Luerzer's Archive - Advertising worldwide|language=en|access-date=2020-04-11}}</ref> and is a Canon EOS Ambassador for India.<ref name=\":10\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.glamflame.net/photography/top-8-fashion-photographers-of-india-in-2018/|title=Top 8 Fashion Photographers Of India In 2018 {{!}} GlamFlame|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-13}}</ref><ref name=\":11\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.schoolofphotography.co.in/best-fashion-photographers-last-one-decade/|title=Best fashion photographers in the last one decade|last=|first=|date=|website=School of photography|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nArjun\u2019s photography style in Fashion and Beauty had made him one of the celebrated photographers in India.<ref name=\":11\" /><ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.socialketchup.in/photographers-of-the-decade/|title=11 Photographers of the decade who captured our hearts|last=Parmar|first=Priyanka|date=2019-12-12|website=Social Ketchup|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-11}}</ref>\n\nArjun\u2019s work was curated at the \u2018BEST OF SHOW\u2019 exhibition in New York during the [[Lucie Awards|LUCIE AWARDS]] Week at [[Zankel Hall]]<ref name=\":4\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.luciefoundation.org/2017-lucie-week-events-announced-oct-25-29/|title=2017 Lucie Week Events Announced, Oct. 25-29|date=2017-10-20|website=Lucie Foundation|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-11}}</ref>, a coveted collective attended by [[Peter Lindbergh]] and other artists of eminence.<ref name=\":5\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.magazzinifotografici.it/ipa-international-photography-award-best-of-show-2017/|title=IPA \u2013 International Photography Award \u2013 BEST of SHOW 2017 {{!}} Magazzini Fotografici|language=it-IT|access-date=2020-04-11}}</ref><ref name=\":6\">{{Cite book|last=|first=|title=International Photography Awards 2017|publisher=IPA|year=2017|isbn=|location=CA 90004, USA|pages=pages 2 and 4}}</ref> In 2017, he was awarded 1st place at the Lucie Awards held in New York in the category, ''\u2018Advertising & Beauty'''. <ref name=\":7\">{{Cite journal|last=IPA *17|first=|date=2017|title=IPA *17|url=https://photoawards.com/books/ipa17.pdf|journal=PhotoAwards.com|volume=|pages=|via=}}</ref>\n\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Arjun Mark\n| image              = Arjun Mark Photographer.jpg\n| caption            = Arjun Mark at his studio in 2018\n| birth_date         = 1980\n| birth_place        = South India\n| nationality        = Indian\n| occupation         = Fashion Photographer\n| website            = http://www.arjunmark.com\n}}\n\n== Early life and background ==\nArjun Mark was born in the southernmost part of India and he grew up moving across towns and cities within [[South India]]. His mother was an artist and hence it is from her where Arjun acquired a flair for art.\n\nAfter schooling, he enrolled for a Bachelor\u2019s degree in Computer Science which he discontinued in a year to peruse a three-year Bachelor\u2019s degree in [[Visual communication|Visual Communication]] in [[Loyola College, Chennai|Loyola College]], [[Chennai]]. This is where he got introduced to photography for the first time. Since then, there was no looking back from photography as this medium of art made him discern another altogether unexpected side of him and has become the premise of his artistic exploration.\n\nDuring college Arjun was very interested in scientific [[high-speed photography]]. His inspiration was [[Harold Eugene Edgerton]]. He experimented capturing water splash and speeding air-gun pellets in his room with [[Do it yourself|DIY]] sound triggers and [[Motion detector|motion detectors]]. All of these experiments were done with conventional film [[Digital single-lens reflex camera|DSLR]] cameras. To fund his film rolls and equipment during college, he worked as a part-time freelance photographer shooting fashion shows and events.\n\n== Early Career ==\nArjun used to apprentice photographers part-time during college. After completing his degree in B.Sc [[Visual communication|Visual Communication]] at [[Loyola College, Chennai|Loyola college]] in 2004, he was a full-time apprentice with a photographer in Chennai. He had worked with him for two years before branching out independently in 2007. Later, Arjun worked independently on assignments in Chennai for almost two years. He was at the same time, looking out to move to a larger market in a larger city.\n\nHe received an opportunity to apprentice under a reputed fashion photographer based in [[Mumbai]]. Arjun shut shop in Chennai in 2009 and moved to Mumbai immediately where he apprenticed for two years. Later, Arjun independently branched out in Mumbai in 2011.\n\n== Recent Career ==\nOver the years, Arjun\u2019s photography style had evolved and progressed of find his niche in Fashion and Beauty, that had made him one of the highly celebrated photographers in India. <ref name=\":0\" /><ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.socialketchup.in/photographers-of-the-decade/|title=Photographers of the decade who captured our hearts|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nArjun has worked with leading international editorial publications such as [[GQ]], [[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue]], [[Elle (magazine)|ELLE]], various fashion labels, [[Bollywood]] celebrities and sports personalities. <ref name=\":3\">{{Cite web|url=http://fashionphotographersmumbai.com/blog/2017/12/12/top-10-fashion-photographers-of-india/|title=Top 10 Fashion Photographers of India|last=admin|date=2017-12-12|website=Fashion Photography Blog|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-11}}</ref>\n\nHis current gamut of work includes well recognised campaigns for Indian and International cosmetic brands such as [[Est\u00e9e Lauder Companies|Estee Lauder]], [[Clinique]], [[Nivea]], [[Lakm\u00e9 Cosmetics|Lakme]]\u00b4, [[Vaseline]] and [[Pond's|Ponds]].\n\nArjun is listed in the [[L\u00fcrzer's Archive|L\u00fcrzer\u2019s Archive]] 200 Best Ad Photographers Worldwide 2020/21, which is the world\u2019s leading publication for outstanding advertising.<ref name=\":8\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.prweb.com/releases/2013/12/prweb11393219.htm|title=200 Best Ad Photographers \u2013 L\u00fcrzer\u2019s Archive Showcases Recent Work Shot By The World\u2019s Best Ad Photographers|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nOne of his most distinguished assignments in 2014 was to photograph [[Jeff Bezos]] for the cover page of [[GQ (Indian edition)|GQ]] magazine.<ref name=\":3\" />\n\n== Awards and Acclaim ==\n\n=== 2020 ===\nArjun was listed in '''L\u00dcRZER'S ARCHIVE 200 Best Ad Photographers Worldwide, Volume 2020/21'''<ref name=\":2\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://arjunmark.com/awards-acclaim/|title=Awards & Acclaim \u2013 ARJUN MARK|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-11}}</ref>[http://arjunmark.com/awards-acclaim/] for the third time. L\u00fcrzer's Archive is the world\u2019s leading publication for outstanding advertising in the industry.<ref name=\":8\" />\n[[File:ArjunMark_Lurzers-Archive-200BEST.jpg|thumb|Listed in L\u00dcRZER'S ARCHIVE 200 Best Ad Photographers Worldwide, Volume  2020/21.]]\n\n=== 2018 ===\nThe prestigious '''''PX3, PARIS''''' ''([[Px3|Prix de la Photographie]])'' honoured Arjun with a '''''SILVER''''' for his fashion story ''\"Fetish Fashion\".''<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://px3.fr/winners/px3/2018/|title=Single Winner|website=PX3 Photography Awards|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://px3.fr/submit/login.php|title=Paris Photo Awards|website=px3.fr|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref> His winning pictures were displayed at the [https://www.espacebeaurepaire.com/ Espace Beaurepaire], France in July 2018.\nFor the second time, Arjun had been listed once again in '''L\u00dcRZER'S ARCHIVE'S 200 Best Ad Photographers Worldwide, Volume 2018/19,'''<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.luerzersarchive.com/en/magazine/print-detail/arjun-mark-66270.html|title=Arjun Mark|website=Luerzer's Archive - Advertising worldwide|language=en|access-date=2020-04-11}}</ref> chosen for one of his self-commissioned assignments featuring a beauty feature with nuns.[[File:ArjunMark_LURZER'S_ARCHIVE_200_Best_Ad_Photographers_Worldwide.jpg|thumb|Published in L\u00dcRZER'S ARCHIVE 200 Best Ad Photographers Worldwide, Volume 2018/19]]\nHe had also received '''''1 Honourable Mention''''' in ''<nowiki/>'Beauty'<nowiki/>'', and '''''1 Honourable Menti''on''' in the ''<nowiki/>'Nude'<nowiki/>'' category this year at the '''[[International Photography Awards|IPA 2018]]'''.\n\n=== 2017 ===\nArjun\u2019s work was curated at the '''''\u2018BEST OF SHOW\u2019''''' exhibition in New York during the [[Lucie Awards|'''LUCIE AWARDS''']] Week at [[Zankel Hall]]<ref name=\":4\" />, a coveted collective attended by [[Peter Lindbergh]] and other artists of eminence<ref name=\":5\" /><ref name=\":6\" />. \n[[File:Curated_at_the_\u2018BEST_OF_SHOW\u2019_exhibition_in_New_York,_that_had_won_1st_place_at_the_IPA(Lucie_Awards).jpg|thumb|Curated at the \u2018BEST OF SHOW\u2019 exhibition in New York, that had won 1st place at the IPA(Lucie Awards).]]\nArjun received '''''1ST PLACE''''' at the '''(IPA)''' '''LUCIE AWARDS''' in the category, 'Advertising and Beauty', from the series \"WATERCOLOUR\".<ref name=\":7\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.photoawards.com/winner/zoom.php?eid=8-143136-17|title=IPA 2017 Winner / WaterColour / Arjun Mark / Arjun Mark|website=www.photoawards.com|access-date=2020-04-12}}</ref> \n\nBesides the above mentioned, one of Arjun's pictures received a '''Honourable Mention''' in the ''<nowiki/>'Nude''' category. \n\n=== 2014 ===\nArjun won '''''2ND PLACE'',''' and was honoured with a '''''<nowiki/>'Merit Of Excellence\"''''' in the category ''<nowiki/>'Fashion'<nowiki/>'' at the '''9th ANNUAL''' '''[https://www.thespiderawards.com/ BLACK AND WHITE SPIDER AWARDS].''' Spider Awards celebrates photographers who operate at the highest levels of their craft and is the leading international award honouring excellence in black and white photography.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thespiderawards.com/resources-winners-press.php|title=Press Release - The Spider Awards|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> [https://www.thespiderawards.com/resources-winners-press.php (Press release)]\n\nOther achievements this year include '''''1 Honourable Mention''''' and '''''6 Nominations''''' in ''Fashion and Beauty'' category at the Spider Awards.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thespiderawards.com/gallery/9th/search?t=arjun+mark&o=a&Submit=Search|title=9th Winners Gallery {{!}} Spider Awards|website=www.thespiderawards.com|access-date=2020-04-12}}</ref>\n\n=== 2013 ===\nArjun was one of the jury on the panel of the Black & White [https://www.thegalaawards.com/ WPGA Awards].<ref name=\":9\">{{Cite web|url=https://gerger.com/about/awards/581398/::/24528::/40584|title=Ger Ger - B&W Photographer of the Year Nominee, WPGA, UK|website=gerger.com|access-date=2020-04-12}}</ref>\n\nHis work was chosen to be showcased at the 9th year of KAPA([https://www.heinzbaumann.com/photoblog/?p=1108 The Korea Advertising Photographers Association]) International Advertising Photography Exhibition held in Seoul.\n\n=== 2012 ===\nArjun's advertising campaign for a luxury fine jewellery brand '[https://www.farahkhanworld.com/ Farah Khan]', was listed in '''L\u00dcRZER'S ARCHIVE 200 Best Ad Photographers Worldwide, Volume 2012/13.'''<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.luerzersarchive.com/en/magazine/print-detail/farah-khan-fine-jewellery-49742.html|title=Farah Khan Fine Jewellery|website=Luerzer's Archive - Advertising worldwide|language=en|access-date=2020-04-12}}</ref> L\u00fcrzer's Archive 200 BEST is the world\u2019s leading publication for outstanding advertising photography in the industry.<ref name=\":8\" />\n\n=== 2011 ===\nIn March 2011, Arjun Mark was credited with the prestigious '''''\u201cAward of Excellence\u201d''''' title at the '''COMMUNICATION ARTS''' in the Advertising category'''.''' His winning project '[http://www.farahkhanworld.com Farah Khan Fine Jewellery'] has been published in the internationally acclaimed publication '''\"Communication Arts, Photography Annual 2011\u201d.'''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.commarts.com/project/18984/farah-khan-fine-jewellery|title=Farah Khan Fine Jewellery|website=Communication Arts|language=en-us|access-date=2020-04-12}}</ref>\n\nArjun was one of the jury on the panel of the Black & White [https://www.thegalaawards.com/ WPGA Awards]<ref name=\":9\" />, with the likes of [http://www.davidzimmerman.com/ David Zimmerman]. \n\nHis work had been published in The [https://photopaper.world/about/ PHOTO PAPER] magazine, Germany.\n\nHe also received '''''2 Nominations''''' at the International Photography Master\u2019s Cup and '''''1 Nomination''''' at the Black and White Spider Awards.\n\n=== 2010 ===\nArjun received an '''''\u201cAward of Excellence\u201d''''' in the portrait category for a self-commissioned project on South Indian Tribes. His work was published in the internationally acclaimed publication '''\"Communication Arts, Best of Photography Annual 2010\".''' \n\nAt the [https://www.thegalaawards.com/ WPGA](Worldwide Photography Gala Awards), he was the '''''WINNER''''' and '''''BEST OF SHOW''.''' \n\nArjun received '''''2 Honourable Mentions''''' at the '''[https://px3.fr/ PX3 Paris],''' a total of '''''9 Honourable Mentions''''' at the '''IPA([https://www.colorawards.com/ International Color Awards])''', and '''''2 Nominations''''' at the '''International Photography Master\u2019s Cup'''.\n\n== Personal Life ==\nArjun is an avid [[Sport Fishing|sport-fishing]] enthusiast<ref name=\":10\" />, and an ardent [[Ocean life]] and [[Wildlife]] lover. \n\n== External Links ==\n[http://www.arjunmark.com Official website] of Arjun Mark \n\n[https://www.femina.in/fashion/fashion-news/four-established-professionals-share-their-success-mantras-129354-1.html Femina July 2019 Issue] - Four established professional share their success mantras\n\n[https://www.thepeacockmagazine.com/photographer-in-focus-arjun-mark/ Peacock Magazine Interview] - PHOTOGRAPHER IN FOCUS: ARJUN MARK\n\n[https://www.hindustantimes.com/art-and-culture/world-photography-day-top-indian-photographers-share-their-iconic-pics/story-fjkVDxUVUr7UNcbWkV5YGM.html HindustanTimes News Article] - Top Indian photographers on World Photography Day\n\n[https://www.glamflame.net/photography/top-8-fashion-photographers-of-india-in-2018/ Online Blog] - Top 8 Fashion Photographers Of India In 2018\n\n== References ==\n<references />\n", "text_old": "= Arjun Mark =\n'''Arjun Mark''' (born 1980) is an acclaimed Indian [[Fashion photography|fashion photographer]] regarded for his bold and modern aesthetic. He is recognised for being listed on '''[[L\u00fcrzer's Archive|L\u00dcRZER'S ARCHIVE'S]]''' 200 Best Ad Photographers Worldwide 2020/21<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.luerzersarchive.com/en/magazine/print-detail/arjun-mark-70877.html|title=Arjun Mark|website=Luerzer's Archive - Advertising worldwide|language=en|access-date=2020-04-11}}</ref> and is a Canon EOS Ambassador for India.<ref name=\":10\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.glamflame.net/photography/top-8-fashion-photographers-of-india-in-2018/|title=Top 8 Fashion Photographers Of India In 2018 {{!}} GlamFlame|language=en-US|ac