on assignments in Chennai for almost two years. He was at the same time, looking out to move to a larger market in a larger city.\n\nHe received an opportunity to apprentice under a reputed fashion photographer based in [[Mumbai]]. Arjun shut shop in Chennai in 2009 and moved to Mumbai immediately where he apprenticed for two years. Later, Arjun independently branched out in Mumbai in 2011.\n\n== Recent Career ==\nOver the years, Arjun\u2019s photography style had evolved and progressed of find his niche in Fashion and Beauty, that had made him one of the highly celebrated photographers in India. <ref name=\":0\" /><ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.socialketchup.in/photographers-of-the-decade/|title=Photographers of the decade who captured our hearts|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nArjun has worked with leading international editorial publications such as [[GQ]], [[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue]], [[Elle (magazine)|ELLE]], various fashion labels, [[Bollywood]] celebrities and sports personalities. <ref name=\":3\">{{Cite web|url=http://fashionphotographersmumbai.com/blog/2017/12/12/top-10-fashion-photographers-of-india/|title=Top 10 Fashion Photographers of India|last=admin|date=2017-12-12|website=Fashion Photography Blog|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-11}}</ref>\n\nHis current gamut of work includes well recognised campaigns for Indian and International cosmetic brands such as [[Est\u00e9e Lauder Companies|Estee Lauder]], [[Clinique]], [[Nivea]], [[Lakm\u00e9 Cosmetics|Lakme]]\u00b4, [[Vaseline]] and [[Pond's|Ponds]].\n\nArjun is listed in the [[L\u00fcrzer's Archive|L\u00fcrzer\u2019s Archive]] 200 Best Ad Photographers Worldwide 2020/21, which is the world\u2019s leading publication for outstanding advertising.<ref name=\":8\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.prweb.com/releases/2013/12/prweb11393219.htm|title=200 Best Ad Photographers \u2013 L\u00fcrzer\u2019s Archive Showcases Recent Work Shot By The World\u2019s Best Ad Photographers|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nOne of his most distinguished assignments in 2014 was to photograph [[Jeff Bezos]] for the cover page of [[GQ (Indian edition)|GQ]] magazine.<ref name=\":3\" />\n\n== Awards and Acclaim ==\n\n=== 2020 ===\nArjun was listed in '''L\u00dcRZER'S ARCHIVE 200 Best Ad Photographers Worldwide, Volume 2020/21'''<ref name=\":2\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://arjunmark.com/awards-acclaim/|title=Awards & Acclaim \u2013 ARJUN MARK|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-11}}</ref>[http://arjunmark.com/awards-acclaim/] for the third time. L\u00fcrzer's Archive is the world\u2019s leading publication for outstanding advertising in the industry.<ref name=\":8\" />\n[[File:ArjunMark_Lurzers-Archive-200BEST.jpg|thumb|Listed in L\u00dcRZER'S ARCHIVE 200 Best Ad Photographers Worldwide, Volume  2020/21.]]\n\n=== 2018 ===\nThe prestigious '''''PX3, PARIS''''' ''([[Px3|Prix de la Photographie]])'' honoured Arjun with a '''''SILVER''''' for his fashion story ''\"Fetish Fashion\".''<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://px3.fr/winners/px3/2018/|title=Single Winner|website=PX3 Photography Awards|language=en-US|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://px3.fr/submit/login.php|title=Paris Photo Awards|website=px3.fr|access-date=2020-04-16}}</ref> His winning pictures were displayed at the [https://www.espacebeaurepaire.com/ Espace Beaurepaire], France in July 2018.\n\n\nFor the second time, Arjun had been listed once again in '''L\u00dcRZER'S ARCHIVE'S 200 Best Ad Photographers Worldwide, Volume 2018/19,'''<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.luerzersarchive.com/en/magazine/print-detail/arjun-mark-66270.html|title=Arjun Mark|website=Luerzer's Archive - Advertising worldwide|language=en|access-date=2020-04-11}}</ref> chosen for one of his self-commissioned assignments featuring a beauty feature with nuns. [[File:ArjunMark_LURZER'S_ARCHIVE_200_Best_Ad_Photographers_Worldwide.jpg|thumb|Published in L\u00dcRZER'S ARCHIVE 200 Best Ad Photographers Worldwide, Volume 2018/19]]\nHe had also received '''''1 Honourable Mention''''' in ''<nowiki/>'Beauty'<nowiki/>'', and '''''1 Honourable Menti''on''' in the ''<nowiki/>'Nude'<nowiki/>'' category this year at the '''[[International Photography Awards|IPA 2018]]'''.\n\n=== 2017 ===\nArjun\u2019s work was curated at the '''''\u2018BEST OF SHOW\u2019''''' exhibition in New York during the [[Lucie Awards|'''LUCIE AWARDS''']] Week at [[Zankel Hall]]<ref name=\":4\" />, a coveted collective attended by [[Peter Lindbergh]] and other artists of eminence<ref name=\":5\" /><ref name=\":6\" />. \n[[File:Curated_at_the_\u2018BEST_OF_SHOW\u2019_exhibition_in_New_York,_that_had_won_1st_place_at_the_IPA(Lucie_Awards).jpg|thumb|Curated at the \u2018BEST OF SHOW\u2019 exhibition in New York, that had won 1st place at the IPA(Lucie Awards).]]\nArjun received '''''1ST PLACE''''' at the '''(IPA)''' '''LUCIE AWARDS''' in the category, 'Advertising and Beauty', from the series \"WATERCOLOUR\".<ref name=\":7\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.photoawards.com/winner/zoom.php?eid=8-143136-17|title=IPA 2017 Winner / WaterColour / Arjun Mark / Arjun Mark|website=www.photoawards.com|access-date=2020-04-12}}</ref> \n\nBesides the above mentioned, one of Arjun's pictures received a '''Honourable Mention''' in the ''<nowiki/>'Nude''' category. \n\n=== 2014 ===\nArjun won '''''2ND PLACE'',''' and was honoured with a '''''<nowiki/>'Merit Of Excellence\"''''' in the category ''<nowiki/>'Fashion'<nowiki/>'' at the '''9th ANNUAL''' '''[https://www.thespiderawards.com/ BLACK AND WHITE SPIDER AWARDS].''' Spider Awards celebrates photographers who operate at the highest levels of their craft and is the leading international award honouring excellence in black and white photography.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thespiderawards.com/resources-winners-press.php|title=Press Release - The Spider Awards|last=|first=|date=|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> [https://www.thespiderawards.com/resources-winners-press.php (Press release)]\n\nOther achievements this year include '''''1 Honourable Mention''''' and '''''6 Nominations''''' in ''Fashion and Beauty'' category at the Spider Awards.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thespiderawards.com/gallery/9th/search?t=arjun+mark&o=a&Submit=Search|title=9th Winners Gallery {{!}} Spider Awards|website=www.thespiderawards.com|access-date=2020-04-12}}</ref>\n\n=== 2013 ===\nArjun was one of the jury on the panel of the Black & White [https://www.thegalaawards.com/ WPGA Awards].<ref name=\":9\">{{Cite web|url=https://gerger.com/about/awards/581398/::/24528::/40584|title=Ger Ger - B&W Photographer of the Year Nominee, WPGA, UK|website=gerger.com|access-date=2020-04-12}}</ref>\n\nHis work was chosen to be showcased at the 9th year of KAPA([https://www.heinzbaumann.com/photoblog/?p=1108 The Korea Advertising Photographers Association]) International Advertising Photography Exhibition held in Seoul.\n\n=== 2012 ===\nArjun's advertising campaign for a luxury fine jewellery brand '[https://www.farahkhanworld.com/ Farah Khan]', was listed in '''L\u00dcRZER'S ARCHIVE 200 Best Ad Photographers Worldwide, Volume 2012/13.'''<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.luerzersarchive.com/en/magazine/print-detail/farah-khan-fine-jewellery-49742.html|title=Farah Khan Fine Jewellery|website=Luerzer's Archive - Advertising worldwide|language=en|access-date=2020-04-12}}</ref> L\u00fcrzer's Archive 200 BEST is the world\u2019s leading publication for outstanding advertising photography in the industry.<ref name=\":8\" />\n\n=== 2011 ===\nIn March 2011, Arjun Mark was credited with the prestigious '''''\u201cAward of Excellence\u201d''''' title at the '''COMMUNICATION ARTS''' in the Advertising category'''.''' His winning project '[http://www.farahkhanworld.com Farah Khan Fine Jewellery'] has been published in the internationally acclaimed publication '''\"Communication Arts, Photography Annual 2011\u201d.'''<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.commarts.com/project/18984/farah-khan-fine-jewellery|title=Farah Khan Fine Jewellery|website=Communication Arts|language=en-us|access-date=2020-04-12}}</ref>\n\nArjun was one of the jury on the panel of the Black & White [https://www.thegalaawards.com/ WPGA Awards]<ref name=\":9\" />, with the likes of [http://www.davidzimmerman.com/ David Zimmerman]. \n\nHis work had been published in The [https://photopaper.world/about/ PHOTO PAPER] magazine, Germany.\n\nHe also received '''''2 Nominations''''' at the International Photography Master\u2019s Cup and '''''1 Nomination''''' at the Black and White Spider Awards.\n\n=== 2010 ===\nArjun received an '''''\u201cAward of Excellence\u201d''''' in the portrait category for a self-commissioned project on South Indian Tribes. His work was published in the internationally acclaimed publication '''\"Communication Arts, Best of Photography Annual 2010\".''' \n\nAt the [https://www.thegalaawards.com/ WPGA](Worldwide Photography Gala Awards), he was the '''''WINNER''''' and '''''BEST OF SHOW''.''' \n\nArjun received '''''2 Honourable Mentions''''' at the '''[https://px3.fr/ PX3 Paris],''' a total of '''''9 Honourable Mentions''''' at the '''IPA([https://www.colorawards.com/ International Color Awards])''', and '''''2 Nominations''''' at the '''International Photography Master\u2019s Cup'''.\n\n== Personal Life ==\nArjun is an avid [[Sport Fishing|sport-fishing]] enthusiast<ref name=\":10\" />, and an ardent [[Ocean life]] and [[Wildlife]] lover. \n\n== External Links ==\n[http://www.arjunmark.com Official website] of Arjun Mark \n\n[https://www.femina.in/fashion/fashion-news/four-established-professionals-share-their-success-mantras-129354-1.html Femina July 2019 Issue] - Four established professional share their success mantras\n\n[https://www.thepeacockmagazine.com/photographer-in-focus-arjun-mark/ Peacock Magazine Interview] - PHOTOGRAPHER IN FOCUS: ARJUN MARK\n\n[https://www.hindustantimes.com/art-and-culture/world-photography-day-top-indian-photographers-share-their-iconic-pics/story-fjkVDxUVUr7UNcbWkV5YGM.html HindustanTimes News Article] - Top Indian photographers on World Photography Day\n\n[https://www.glamflame.net/photography/top-8-fashion-photographers-of-india-in-2018/ Online Blog] - Top 8 Fashion Photographers Of India In 2018\n\n== References ==\n<references />\n", "name_user": "I.leslee", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Arjun_Mark"}
{"title_page": "Vasili Byros", "text_new": "<!-- Please do not remove or change this AfD message until the discussion has been closed. -->\n{{Article for deletion/dated|page=Vasili Byros|timestamp=20200411073339|year=2020|month=April|day=11|substed=yes|help=off}}\n<!-- Once discussion is closed, please place on talk page: {{Old AfD multi|page=Vasili Byros|date=11 April 2020|result='''keep'''}} -->\n<!-- End of AfD message, feel free to edit beyond this point -->\n{{Orphan|date=April 2020}}\n\n'''Vasili Byros''' (born 1976) is a [[Greek Americans|Greek-American]] [[music theory|music theorist]], [[musicology|musicologist]] and [[pianist]].<ref name=nytimesprofile>[https://www.nytimes.com/2003/05/28/nyregion/to-graduation-tossing-obstacles-aside-869198.html To Graduation, Tossing Obstacles Aside] New York Times Profile</ref> He is best known for his contributions to the field of music schemata theory and [[partimento]].<ref name=award>[https://www.music.northwestern.edu/news/2017/byros-recognized-outstanding-publication-award Prelude on a Partimento Award] Northwestern University</ref>\n\n==Education==\nByros is an alumni of the [[Aaron Copland School of Music]], receiving his B.A. in [[music composition]] in 2001 and M.A. in [[music history]] and music theory in 2003. Byros received his Ph.D in Music Theory from [[Yale School of Music|Yale University]] in 2009. He is currently a tenured Associate Professor of Music Theory and Cognition at Northwestern University since 2010, after spending a year at the [[Jacobs School of Music|Jacobs School of Music of Indiana University]] as a Post-Doctoral Resident Scholar.<ref name=jobtitle>[https://www.music.northwestern.edu/faculty/profile/vasili-byros Northwestern Bienen School of Music] Northwestern Faculty Page</ref> In 2017, Byros received the Charles Deering McCormick Professor of Teaching Excellence.<ref name=teachingaward>[https://www.northwestern.edu/provost/faculty-honors/university-teaching-awards/award-recipients/2017.html#byros Northwestern Office of the Provost] Charles Deering McCormick Professor of Teaching Excellence</ref>\n\n== Research related to Music Schemata Theory ==\n===Le Sol Fi Sol===\nOne of Byros' notable contributions to Music Schemata Theory is his study of the ''Le-Sol-Fi-Sol'' Schema in [[Ludwig van Beethoven]]'s [[Symphony No. 3 (Beethoven)|Eroica Symphony]].<ref name=magarotto>[https://muse.jhu.edu/article/601075 The Oxford Handbook of Topic Theory ed. by Danuta Mirka] Review by Matteo Magarotto</ref><ref name=rice>[https://jams.ucpress.edu/content/68/2/446.abstract The Oxford Handbook of Topic Theory ed. by Danuta Mirka] Review by John A. Rice</ref>\n\n[[File:Le Sol Fi Sol Example.jpg|thumb|left|500px|An example of the Le-Sol-Fi-Sol Schema in Mozart's Requiem]]\n{{clear|left}}\n\n===Fonte-Romanesca===\nByros is also noted for identifying and naming a common music schema popularized by [[Arcangelo Corelli]] and still used a century later by [[Wolfgang Amadeus Mozart]] known as the ''Fonte-Romanesca'', which shares the characteristics of a ''Fonte''<ref name=fonte>[http://partimenti.org/schemas/collections/index.html Compendia of Schemas] Schemas in the Galant Style by Robert Gjerdingen</ref> and a [[Romanesca]].<ref name=fonteromanesca>[https://www.academia.edu/36154658/Mozarts_Vintage_Corelli_The_Microstory_of_a_Fonte-Romanesca Society for Music Theory] Mozart's Vintage Corelli</ref>\n\n[[File:Corelli Fonte-Romanesca.jpg|thumb|left|500px|An example of the Fonte-Romanesca Schema by Arcangelo Corelli]]\n{{clear|left}}\n\n==Awards==\n* '''Outstanding Publication Award''' (2017) - ''Prelude on a Partimento: Invention in the Compositional Pedagogy of the German States in the Time of J. S. Bach'' - Society for Music Theory.<ref name=publicationaward>[https://societymusictheory.org/sites/default/files/newsletters/41-1.pdf Society for Music Theory] Outstanding Publication Award, 2017</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[Partimento]]\n* [[John A. Rice (musicologist)]]\n* [[Robert Gjerdingen]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== Further reading ==\n{{refbegin|3}}\n* {{citation |last=Byros |title=Towards an \"Archaeology\" of Hearing: Schemata and Eighteenth-Century Consciousness |publisher=Korean Institute for Musicology, Musica Humana, Autumn 2009, Vol. 1, No. 2, 235\u2013306 |url= https://www.academia.edu/893638 |year=2009}}\n* {{citation |last=Byros |title=Meyer's Anvil: Revisiting the Schema Concept |journal=Music Analysis |publisher=Musical Analysis, 31/iii, Blackwell Publishing Ltd |url= https://www.academia.edu/2477056 |doi= 10.1111/j.1468-2249.2012.00344.x|year=2012|volume=31 |issue=3 |pages=273\u2013346 }}\n* {{citation |last=Byros |title=Topics and Harmonic Schemata: A Case from Beethoven |publisher=The Oxford Handbook of Topic Theory, pp. 381\u2013414 |url= https://www.academia.edu/9050311 |year=2014}}\n* {{citation |last=Byros |title=\"'Hauptruhepuncte des Geistes': Punctuation Schemas and the Late-Eighteenth-Century Sonata,\" In *What Is a Cadence?: Theoretical and Analytical Perspectives on Cadences in the Classical Repertoire |publisher=Leuven University Press, pp. 215\u2013251 |url= https://www.academia.edu/12618637 |year=2015}}\n* {{citation |last=Byros| first=Vasili|title=Prelude on a Partimento: Invention in the Compositional Pedagogy of the German States in the Time of J. S. Bach | journal=Music Theory Online|publisher= Society for Music Theory, Volume 21, Number 3 | url=https://www.mtosmt.org/issues/mto.15.21.3/mto.15.21.3.byros.html |year=2015| volume=21| issue=3| doi=10.30535/mto.21.3.3}}\n* {{citation |last=Byros |title=Mozart's Vintage Corelli: The Microstory of a Fonte-Romanesca |journal=Int\u00e9gral |publisher=Int\u00e9gral, 31, 63-89 |url= https://www.academia.edu/36154658 |year=2017}}\n{{refend}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://vasilibyros.com/ Vasili Byros] Personal Page.\n* [https://www.music.northwestern.edu/faculty/profile/vasili-byros Vasili Byros] Faculty page at the Northwestern Bienen School of Music.\n* {{Google Scholar id | id= Sl8zkeEAAAAJ | name= Vasili Byros }}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Byros, Vasili}}\n[[Category:American music theorists]]\n[[Category:Music theorists]]\n[[Category:20th-century musicologists]]\n[[Category:21st-century musicologists]]\n[[Category:Northwestern University faculty]]\n[[Category:Indiana University staff]]\n[[Category:Yale University alumni]]\n[[Category:1976 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n", "text_old": "<!-- Please do not remove or change this AfD message until the discussion has been closed. -->\n{{Article for deletion/dated|page=Vasili Byros|timestamp=20200411073339|year=2020|month=April|day=11|substed=yes|help=off}}\n<!-- Once discussion is closed, please place on talk page: {{Old AfD multi|page=Vasili Byros|date=11 April 2020|result='''keep'''}} -->\n<!-- End of AfD message, feel free to edit beyond this point -->\n{{Orphan|date=April 2020}}\n\n'''Vasili Byros''' (born 1976) is a Greek-American [[music theory|music theorist]], [[musicology|musicologist]] and [[pianist]].<ref name=nytimesprofile>[https://www.nytimes.com/2003/05/28/nyregion/to-graduation-tossing-obstacles-aside-869198.html To Graduation, Tossing Obstacles Aside] New York Times Profile</ref> He is best known for his contributions to the field of music schemata theory and [[partimento]].<ref name=award>[https://www.music.northwestern.edu/news/2017/byros-recognized-outstanding-publication-award Prelude on a Partimento Award] Northwestern University</ref>\n\n==Education==\nByros is an alumni of the [[Aaron Copland School of Music]], receiving his B.A. in [[music composition]] in 2001 and M.A. in [[music history]] and music theory in 2003. Byros received his Ph.D in Music Theory from [[Yale School of Music|Yale University]] in 2009. He is currently a tenured Associate Professor of Music Theory and Cognition at Northwestern University since 2010, after spending a year at the [[Jacobs School of Music|Jacobs School of Music of Indiana University]] as a Post-Doctoral Resident Scholar.<ref name=jobtitle>[https://www.music.northwestern.edu/faculty/profile/vasili-byros Northwestern Bienen School of Music] Northwestern Faculty Page</ref> In 2017, Byros received the Charles Deering McCormick Professor of Teaching Excellence.<ref name=teachingaward>[https://www.northwestern.edu/provost/faculty-honors/university-teaching-awards/award-recipients/2017.html#byros Northwestern Office of the Provost] Charles Deering McCormick Professor of Teaching Excellence</ref>\n\n== Research related to Music Schemata Theory ==\n===Le Sol Fi Sol===\nOne of Byros' notable contributions to Music Schemata Theory is his study of the ''Le-Sol-Fi-Sol'' Schema in [[Ludwig van Beethoven]]'s [[Symphony No. 3 (Beethoven)|Eroica Symphony]].<ref name=magarotto>[https://muse.jhu.edu/article/601075 The Oxford Handbook of Topic Theory ed. by Danuta Mirka] Review by Matteo Magarotto</ref><ref name=rice>[https://jams.ucpress.edu/content/68/2/446.abstract The Oxford Handbook of Topic Theory ed. by Danuta Mirka] Review by John A. Rice</ref>\n\n[[File:Le Sol Fi Sol Example.jpg|thumb|left|500px|An example of the Le-Sol-Fi-Sol Schema in Mozart's Requiem]]\n{{clear|left}}\n\n===Fonte-Romanesca===\nByros is also noted for identifying and naming a common music schema popularized by [[Arcangelo Corelli]] and still used a century later by [[Wolfgang Amadeus Mozart]] known as the ''Fonte-Romanesca'', which shares the characteristics of a ''Fonte''<ref name=fonte>[http://partimenti.org/schemas/collections/index.html Compendia of Schemas] Schemas in the Galant Style by Robert Gjerdingen</ref> and a [[Romanesca]].<ref name=fonteromanesca>[https://www.academia.edu/36154658/Mozarts_Vintage_Corelli_The_Microstory_of_a_Fonte-Romanesca Society for Music Theory] Mozart's Vintage Corelli</ref>\n\n[[File:Corelli Fonte-Romanesca.jpg|thumb|left|500px|An example of the Fonte-Romanesca Schema by Arcangelo Corelli]]\n{{clear|left}}\n\n==Awards==\n* '''Outstanding Publication Award''' (2017) - ''Prelude on a Partimento: Invention in the Compositional Pedagogy of the German States in the Time of J. S. Bach'' - Society for Music Theory.<ref name=publicationaward>[https://societymusictheory.org/sites/default/files/newsletters/41-1.pdf Society for Music Theory] Outstanding Publication Award, 2017</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[Partimento]]\n* [[John A. Rice (musicologist)]]\n* [[Robert Gjerdingen]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== Further reading ==\n{{refbegin|3}}\n* {{citation |last=Byros |title=Towards an \"Archaeology\" of Hearing: Schemata and Eighteenth-Century Consciousness |publisher=Korean Institute for Musicology, Musica Humana, Autumn 2009, Vol. 1, No. 2, 235\u2013306 |url= https://www.academia.edu/893638 |year=2009}}\n* {{citation |last=Byros |title=Meyer's Anvil: Revisiting the Schema Concept |journal=Music Analysis |publisher=Musical Analysis, 31/iii, Blackwell Publishing Ltd |url= https://www.academia.edu/2477056 |doi= 10.1111/j.1468-2249.2012.00344.x|year=2012|volume=31 |issue=3 |pages=273\u2013346 }}\n* {{citation |last=Byros |title=Topics and Harmonic Schemata: A Case from Beethoven |publisher=The Oxford Handbook of Topic Theory, pp. 381\u2013414 |url= https://www.academia.edu/9050311 |year=2014}}\n* {{citation |last=Byros |title=\"'Hauptruhepuncte des Geistes': Punctuation Schemas and the Late-Eighteenth-Century Sonata,\" In *What Is a Cadence?: Theoretical and Analytical Perspectives on Cadences in the Classical Repertoire |publisher=Leuven University Press, pp. 215\u2013251 |url= https://www.academia.edu/12618637 |year=2015}}\n* {{citation |last=Byros| first=Vasili|title=Prelude on a Partimento: Invention in the Compositional Pedagogy of the German States in the Time of J. S. Bach | journal=Music Theory Online|publisher= Society for Music Theory, Volume 21, Number 3 | url=https://www.mtosmt.org/issues/mto.15.21.3/mto.15.21.3.byros.html |year=2015| volume=21| issue=3| doi=10.30535/mto.21.3.3}}\n* {{citation |last