|mi|disp=br}}<br />[[New European Driving Cycle|NEDC]]: {{cvt|480|km|mi|0|disp=br}}\n<!-- 75D   -->| [[FTP-75|EPA]]: {{cvt|259|mi||disp=br}}<br />[[New European Driving Cycle|NEDC]]: {{cvt|490|km|mi|0|disp=br}}\n<!-- 85    -->| [[FTP-75|EPA]]: {{cvt|265|mi|disp=br}}<br />[[New European Driving Cycle|NEDC]]: {{cvt|502|km|disp=br}}\n<!-- 85D   -->| [[FTP-75|EPA]]:\n{{cvt|270|mi|disp=br}}<br />[[New European Driving Cycle|NEDC]]: {{cvt|528|km|disp=br}}\n<!-- P85   -->| [[FTP-75|EPA]]: {{cvt|265|mi|disp=br}}<br />[[New European Driving Cycle|NEDC]]: {{cvt|502|km|disp=br}}\n<!-- P85+  -->|[[FTP-75|EPA]]:\n{{cvt|265|mi|disp=br}}<br />[[New European Driving Cycle|NEDC]]:\n\n<!-- P85D  -->| [[FTP-75|EPA:]]{{cvt|253|mi|disp=br}}<br />[[New European Driving Cycle|NEDC]]: {{cvt|480|km||0|disp=br}}\n\n<!-- P85DL -->| [[FTP-75|EPA]]: {{cvt|253|mi|disp=br}}<br />[[New European Driving Cycle|NEDC]]: {{cvt|480|km||0|disp=br}}\n<!-- 90    -->| [[FTP-75|EPA]]: {{cvt|265|mi|disp=br}}<br />[[New European Driving Cycle|NEDC]]: {{cvt|502|km|disp=br}}\n<!-- 90D   -->| [[FTP-75|EPA]]: {{cvt|294|mi|disp=br}}<br />[[New European Driving Cycle|NEDC]]: {{cvt|528|km|disp=br}}\n<!-- P90D  -->| [[FTP-75|EPA]]: {{cvt|270|mi|disp=br}}<br />[[New European Driving Cycle|NEDC]]: {{cvt|509|km|disp=br}}\n<!-- P90DL -->| [[FTP-75|EPA]]: {{cvt|270|mi|disp=br}}<br />[[New European Driving Cycle|NEDC]]: {{cvt|509|km|disp=br}}\n<!-- P100DL-->| [[FTP-75|EPA]]: {{cvt|315|mi|disp=br||abbr=}}<br />[[New European Driving Cycle|NEDC]]: {{cvt|613|km|disp=br}}\n<!-- 100D  -->| [[FTP-75|EPA]]: {{cvt|335|mi|disp=br||abbr=}}\n<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.fueleconomy.gov/feg/Find.do?action=sbs&id=38640 |title=2017 Tesla Model S AWD - 100D |publisher=US Department of Energy |access-date=November 1, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.roadandtrack.com/new-cars/car-technology/a27254315/tesla-squeezes-370-miles-of-range-out-of-its-big-battery-model-s/ |title=Tesla Squeezes 370 Miles of Range Out of its Big-Battery Model S |first=Bob |last=Sorokanich |work=Road & Track |location=US |date=April 24, 2019 |access-date=May 14, 2019}}</ref>[[New European Driving Cycle|NEDC]]: {{cvt|632|km|disp=br}}\n<!-- Perf  -->| [[FTP-75|EPA]]: {{cvt|348|mi|disp=br||abbr=}}<br />[[New European Driving Cycle|NEDC]]: {{cvt|671|km|disp=br||abbr=}}\n<!-- LRP   -->| [[FTP-75|EPA]]: {{cvt|390|mi|disp=br||abbr=}}\n<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.fueleconomy.gov/feg/Find.do?action=sbs&id=38640 |title=2017 Tesla Model S AWD - 100D |publisher=US Department of Energy |access-date=November 1, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.roadandtrack.com/new-cars/car-technology/a27254315/tesla-squeezes-370-miles-of-range-out-of-its-big-battery-model-s/ |title=Tesla Squeezes 370 Miles of Range Out of its Big-Battery Model S |first=Bob |last=Sorokanich |work=Road & Track |location=US |date=April 24, 2019 |access-date=May 14, 2019}}</ref>[[New European Driving Cycle|NEDC]]: {{cvt|713|km|disp=br||abbr=}}\n|-\n! Max. power, <br />motor\n<!-- 40    -->| {{cvt|285|kW|hp|order=flip|disp=br}}\n<!-- 60    -->| {{cvt|285|kW|hp|order=flip|disp=br}}\n|518&nbsp;hp\n386&nbsp;kW<!-- 70 -->\n| {{cvt|285|kW|hp|order=flip|disp=br}}\n<!-- 70D   -->| {{cvt|386|kW|hp|order=flip|disp=br}}\n<!-- 75    -->| {{cvt|285|kW|hp|order=flip|disp=br}}\n<!-- 75D   -->| {{cvt|386|kW|hp|order=flip|disp=br}}\n<!-- 85    -->| {{cvt|285|kW|hp|order=flip|disp=br}}\n<!-- 85D   -->| {{cvt|386|kW|hp|order=flip|disp=br}}\n<!-- P85   -->| {{cvt|350|kW|hp|0|order=flip|disp=br}}\n|{{cvt|350|kW|hp|0|order=flip|disp=br}}<!-- P85D -->\n| {{cvt|568|kW|hp|disp=br|order=flip}}{{efn|name=motorpower}}\n<!-- P85DL -->| {{cvt|568|kW|hp|order=flip|disp=br}}{{efn|name=ludicrous}}{{efn|name=motorpower}}\n<!-- 90    -->| {{cvt|285|kW|hp|order=flip|disp=br}}\n<!-- 90D   -->| {{cvt|386|kW|hp|order=flip|disp=br}}\n<!-- P90D  -->| {{cvt|568|kW|hp|disp=br|order=flip}}{{efn|name=motorpower}}\n<!-- P90DL -->| {{cvt|568|kW|hp|order=flip|disp=br}}{{efn|name=ludicrous}}{{efn