br}}<!-- 70 -->\n| {{cvt|140|mph|disp=br}}\n<!-- 70D   -->| {{cvt|140|mph|disp=br}}\n<!-- 75    -->| {{cvt|140|mph|disp=br}}\n<!-- 75D   -->| {{cvt|140|mph|disp=br}}\n<!-- 85    -->| {{cvt|140|mph|disp=br}}\n<!-- 85D   -->| {{cvt|155|mph|disp=br}}\n<!-- P85   -->| {{cvt|130|mph|disp=br}}\n|{{cvt|130|mph|disp=br}}<!-- P85D -->\n| {{cvt|155|mph|disp=br}}<ref name=AUspec/>\n<!-- P85DL -->| {{cvt|155|mph|disp=br}}\n<!-- 90    -->| {{cvt|140|mph|disp=br}}\n<!-- 90D   -->| {{cvt|155|mph|disp=br}}<ref name=AUspec/>\n<!-- P90D  -->| {{cvt|155|mph|disp=br}}<ref name=AUspec/>\n<!-- P90DL -->| {{cvt|155|mph|disp=br}}\n<!-- P100DL -->| {{cvt|163|mph|disp=br}}\n<!-- 100D  -->| {{cvt|155|mph|disp=br}}\n<!-- Perf  -->| {{cvt|163|mph|disp=br}}\n<!-- LRP   -->| {{cvt|155|mph|disp=br}}\n|-\n![[Tesla Supercharger|Supercharging]]\n| {{no}}\n| {{partial|Optional{{efn|After purchase, a Supercharging upgrade was available}} }}\n| colspan=\"19\" {{yes|Capability included for all cars.  Fees vary.}}\n|-\n! Availability\n<!-- 40    -->| 2012&nbsp;\u2013 <br />April 2013\n<!-- 60    -->| 2012&nbsp;\u2013 <br />April 2015; <br />June 2016&nbsp;\u2013 <br />April 2017\n<!-- 60D   -->| yes|June 2016&nbsp;\u2013 <br />April 2017\n<!-- 70    -->| April 2015&nbsp;\u2013 <br />May 2016\n<!-- 70D   -->| April 2015&nbsp;\u2013 <br />May 2016\n<!-- 75    -->| May 2016&nbsp;\u2013 <br />September 2017\n<!-- 75D   -->| May 2016&nbsp;\u2013 <br />January 2019\n<!-- 85    -->| 2012&nbsp;\u2013 <br />February 2016\n<!-- 85D   -->| November 2014&nbsp;\u2013 <br />February 2016\n<!-- P85   -->| 2012&nbsp;\u2013 <br />November 2014\n|2012&nbsp;\u2013 <br />November 2014<!-- P85D -->\n| November 2014&nbsp;\u2013 <br />February 2016\n<!-- P85DL -->| August 2015&nbsp;\u2013 <br />February 2016\n<!-- 90   -->| 2015&nbsp;\u2013 <br />2016\n<!-- 90D   -->| August 2015&nbsp;\u2013 <br />June 2017\n<!-- P90D  -->| August 2015&nbsp;\u2013 <br />November 2016\n<!-- P90DL -->| August 2015&nbsp;\u2013<br />August 2016\n<!-- P100DL -->| August 2016&nbsp;\u2013 <br />March 2019\n<!-- 100D  -->| August 2016&nbsp;\u2013 <br />March 2019\n<!-- Perf  -->| {{yes|April 2019&nbsp;\u2013 <br />present}}\n<!-- LRP   -->| {{yes|April 2019&nbsp;\u2013 <br />present}}\n|-\n! style=\"text-align: left; font-size: 0.85em; font-weight: normal; padding: 6px 0 4px 14px;\" colspan=\"22\" | {{notelist}}\n|}\n\n=== Energy consumption ===\nUnder its five-cycle testing protocol, the [[United States Environmental Protection Agency]] (EPA) rated the 90&nbsp;kWh Model S model with a combined [[fuel economy in automobiles|fuel economy]] equivalent of 104&nbsp;MPGe ({{cvt|104.25|mpgus|L/100km|disp=out|2|sp=us}} or {{cvt|104.25|mpgus|mpgimp|disp=out|0|sp=us}}), with an equivalent {{cvt|102|mpgus}} in city driving and {{cvt|107|mpgus}} on highways.<ref name=EPAratings>{{cite web|url=https://www.fueleconomy.gov/feg/Find.do?action=sbs&id=38524&id=38569&id=38525&id=38640 |title=Compare Side-by-Side|work=fueleconomy.gov|publisher=[[U. S. Environmental Protection Agency]] and [[U.S. Department of Energy]]|access-date=April 21, 2017}}</ref>\n\nThe following table shows the EPA's official ratings for fuel economy in [[miles per gallon gasoline equivalent]] (MPGe).\n\n<!-- Note: PEVs sort in descending order by MPGe combined rating, highest MPGe first (electric mode for PHEVS) -->\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n|+ 2012\u201316 Tesla Model S fuel economy\n|-\n! rowspan=2 | Model\n! rowspan=2 | Model<br>year\n! colspan=3 | Fuel economy (MPGe)\n|-\n! Combined\n! City\n! Highway\n|-\n| {{small|60&nbsp;kWh}}<ref name=EPA2015/><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.fueleconomy.gov/feg/Find.do?action=sbs&id=33367&id=33368 |title=2013 Tesla Model S (60 kWh battery pack) |website=Fueleconomy.gov |publisher=[[U. S. Environmental Protection Agency]] and [[U.S. Department of Energy]] |date=December 5, 2012 |access-date=December 7, 2012}}</ref><ref name=ModelS60_70_90/> || 2013\u201315 || 95; <small>35&nbsp;kWh/100&nb